cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) is the most likely category as the paper is about audio signal processing and spectrogram generation.
- cs.SI (Speech and Natural Language Processing) is also a likely category as the paper deals with audio signal processing, which is closely related to speech processing.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper proposes a neural network-based toolbox for audio signal processing.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper deals with real-time on-the-fly audio signal processing.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category as the paper deals with audio signal processing and spectrogram generation, which are important components of multimedia processing.
